Interface Summary

CommonTopologyInfo The class (available through the SystemInfoService4 for local values or the SSHConnection2 and WindowsInfoConnection for remote values) provides values that can be used with the Host and OperatingSystem topology objects.
ConnectionTestCallback<T> Allows agents to register objects to test connections.
Credential A Credential defines authentication attributes for connecting to access controlled resources.
CredentialEvent Interface to be used by credential clients for passing parameters of credential-related errors to the server.
CredentialEventProperties A collection of string property names that are commonly used when calling CredentialEvent.setProperty(java.lang.String, java.lang.String).

ServiceFactory Factory that allocates any type of Service.

ThreadFactoryService This service provides ThreadFactory instances that allow agents to safely create threads.

TimerService.Task

Exception Summary
AgentResourcesInvalidRequestException AgentResourcesInvalidRequestException Thrown when a request for a resource change via the AgentResourceService cannot be applied
ASPModificationException Exception to be throw should an ASP property manipulation error occur.
CommandFailedException An exception thrown when a connection service has detected that a command issued to the remote system has failed.
ConnectionBrokenException Thrown when an established connection to a remote system is no longer working.
ConnectionCancelledException An exception thrown by any of FglAM's remote connection services to indicate that a connection was not made to the target machine because the connection attempt was purposely cancelled for some reason.
ConnectionRefusedException An exception thrown that indicates the remote machine has actively rejected the connection.
CredentialException CredentialExceptions are thrown when an error occurs while working with a Credential
CredentialPolicyViolationException This exception is generated when a CredentialPolicy fails to validate.
CredentialRejectedException Created by IntelliJ IDEA.
HostNotReachableException Thrown when a remote connection service has determined that a remote host cannot be reached.
InvalidCredentialsException A wrapper for all the credential-based exceptions that prevent a connection from being established to a remote machine.
InvalidTopologyException This exception is generated when invalid or incorrect data is passed to the getSubmitter() method of a topology submission service.
NoCredentialsException Created by IntelliJ IDEA.
NonZeroExitCodeException Exception thrown when a process that is being executed exits with a non-zero exit code.
NotLocalAgentException Thrown when a request to control a RemoteAgentProxy through its local instance is not available.
QueryFailedException An exception thrown when a connection service has detected that a query issued to the remote system has failed.
RemoteConnectionException An exception thrown by any of FglAM's remote connection services to indicate that a connection was not made to the target machine.
ServiceException Exception thrown by ServiceFactory when a requested service is not available or if a service method fails in some way.
ServiceFactory.InjectionFailedException Exception generated when a dependency injection fails.
ServiceFactory.ServiceNotAvailableException Exception thrown when the requested service is not available.
SignalledExitException An exception thrown when a process has exited by throwing a signal instead of returning cleanly.
SubmittingTooFrequentlyUnsupportedException An exception thrown to indicate that flushPendingMessages() on a topology submitter is being called too frequently.
TopologyException An base exception class for all exceptions generated from the topology submission services.
TopologyServerOverloadException An exception to indicate that a topology submission cannot be accepted because the server is currently overloaded.
UnixCredentialRejectedException An exception thrown when FglAM has conclusively determined that a connection to a target system has been refused due to configuration issues when connecting from a UNIX system.
UnsupportedCredentialTypeException Indicates that an unsupported Credential type was provided to a service.
UnsupportedRemoteProtocolException An exception thrown by any of FglAM's remote connection services to indicate that a connection was not made to the target machine because the target machine uses an unsupported protocol.
WindowsConnectionRefusedException An exception thrown when FglAM has conclusively determined that a connection to a target system has been refused due to configuration issues when connecting from a Windows system.
WindowsCredentialRejectedException An exception thrown when FglAM has conclusively determined that a credential has been rejected due to configuration issues when connecting from a Windows system.
WMISecuritySettingsException An exception thrown when attempts at executing a WMI query fail due to invalid WMISecuritySettings.
 

Annotation Types Summary
Inject An annotation that can be placed on fields, methods, or constructors to indicate that the dependency injection provided by ServiceFactory should be used to provide a value for the annotated element.
